      "ring_nf\n  · -- Second direction: if g satisfies the condition, then it is in the solution set\n    intro h\n    have h1 := h 1 1\n    rcases h1 with ⟨k, hk⟩\n    have h2 : (g 1 + 1) * (g 1 + 1) = k * k := by\n      nlinarith\n    have h3 : g 1 + 1 = k := by\n      nlinarith\n    have h7 : ∃ c, ∀ x, g x = x + c := by\n      use g 1 - 1\n      intro x\n      have h8 := h x 1\n      rcases h8 with ⟨l, hl⟩\n      have h9 : (g x + 1) * (g 1 + x) = l * l := by\n        nlinarith\n      have h10 : g 1 + 1 = k := by\n        nlinarith\n      have h11 : g x = x + (g 1 - 1) := by\n        nlinarith [sq_nonneg (g x - (x + (g 1 - 1))), sq_nonneg (l - (g 1 + x)), sq_nonneg (g 1 - 1)]\n      simpa using h11\n    simp [h7]",
