We need to determine all functions \( g : \mathbb{Z}^+ \to \mathbb{Z}^+ \) such that \( (g(m) + n)(g(n) + m) \) is always a perfect square.

First, let's think about possible approaches. We need \( (g(m) + n)(g(n) + m) \) to be a perfect square for all \( m, n \in \mathbb{Z}^+ \).

One common approach with symmetric expressions like this is to try specific values for \( m \) and \( n \) to derive properties of \( g \).

