        rw [hc m, hc n]
        all_goals ring
```

Now we need to show that $(m + n + c) \cdot (n + m + c)$ is a perfect square. But this is $(m + n + c)^2$, so it is a perfect square with root $m + n + c$.

So we need to prove that $\text{IsSquare} ((m + n + c) \cdot (n + m + c))$.

The Lean proof would be:

```tactics
